cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper investigates citation behavior and patterns in scientific publications, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, given the focus on interdisciplinary citation patterns and the use of citation projection graphs, we believe that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
